Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @linguine{180%grams}, ~{12%mins}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @diced chorizo{120%grams}, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @tomato puree{30%grams} and @water{75%ml}.

Bring to the boil then simmer, ~{2-3%mins}.

Meanwhile, drain the pasta and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through.

Next, stir the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}, @peas{120%grams} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} into the sauce. Cook so it's piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the cooked pasta.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Serve your pasta in #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%grams} and drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!